  <title>Cogl.MetaTextureCallback</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function onMetaTextureCallback(sub_texture: <link xref="Cogl.Texture">Cogl.Texture</link>, sub_texture_coords: Number(gfloat), meta_coords: Number(gfloat)): void {
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>A callback used with <link xref="Cogl.meta_texture_foreach_in_region"/> to
retrieve details of all the low-level <link xref="Cogl.Texture"/>&lt;!-- --&gt;s that
make up a given <link xref="Cogl.MetaTexture"/>.</p>
  <p>Since 1.10</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>sub_texture</code></title>
  <p>A low-level <link xref="Cogl.Texture"/> making up part of a
              <link xref="Cogl.MetaTexture"/>.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>sub_texture_coords</code></title>
  <p>A float 4-tuple ordered like
                     (tx1,ty1,tx2,ty2) defining what region of the
                     current <code>sub_texture</code> maps to a sub-region of a
                     <link xref="Cogl.MetaTexture"/>. (tx1,ty1) is the top-left
                     sub-region coordinate and (tx2,ty2) is the
                     bottom-right. These are low-level texture
                     coordinates.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>meta_coords</code></title>
  <p>A float 4-tuple ordered like (tx1,ty1,tx2,ty2)
              defining what sub-region of a <link xref="Cogl.MetaTexture"/> this
              low-level <code>sub_texture</code> maps too. (tx1,ty1) is
              the top-left sub-region coordinate and (tx2,ty2) is
              the bottom-right. These are high-level meta-texture
              coordinates.</p>
</item>
</terms>

</page>
